    dc:creator "Emery, Nathan J.; Emery, David L.; Popple, Lindsay W." ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Redescription of Myopsalta atrata (Goding and Froggatt) and Description of Two New Species of Myopsalta Moulds (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) from Central Western New South Wales" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676706>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676718>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676720>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676722>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676714> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676706>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Photos of male left timbals, with dorsal edge at left and posterior margin at bottom: (A) Myopsalta atrata (Goding & Froggatt), Royal National Park (34°06'59\"S 151°03'30\"E); (B) Myopsalta coolahensis sp.nov., Coolah (31°56'25\"S 149°52'18\"E); (C) Myopsalta libritor sp.nov., Merriwa (32°08'19\"S 150°21'00\"E). Scale bars = 200 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4676706/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676718>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Myopsalta coolahensis sp.nov. (A) male, Coolah (31°56'25\"S 149°52'18\"E), dorsal habitus; (B) male, Coolah, ventral habitus; (C) female, Coolah, dorsal habitus; (D) female, Coolah, ventral habitus. Scale bars = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4676718/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676720>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Myopsalta coolahensis—illustration of male pygofer and internal genitalia;(A) viewed laterally from the left;(B) viewed ventrally;(D) aedeagus,lateral view; and (D) aedeagus, rotated 30° left from central view C. See caption to Fig. 3 for abbreviations." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4676720/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676722>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Male calling song structures of Myopsalta coolahensis sp.nov., illustrated in waveform plot form. Each lower plot is expanded from the one above, to illustrate the finer temporal structure of each song comparison.The spectrogram at the bottom of the figure displays song frequency, which exhibits no modulation between the song components in this species. This specimen was recorded by NJE in the field near Coolah (31°56'25\"S 149°52'18\"E) at 10h30 on 14 November 2014." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4676722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4676714>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Map of eastern Australia showing the geographical distribution of M. atrata (closed circles), M. coolahensis sp.nov. (open squares) and M. libritor sp.nov. (closed triangles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4676714/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

